+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016Fggr3CWUgux7YKr82fn8b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The naive question that cracks this open: **\"What IS a branch, really?\"**\n\nA branch is just a named container holding its own copy of all documents and their version histories. When you create a branch, you snapshot the current state. The \"common ancestor\" is literally just that snapshot. I don't need a complex DAG or commit graph. Each branch stores:\n- Its documents (current state)\n- Version histories per document\n- A snapshot of what it looked like at branch creation time (the fork point)\n\nThe merge algorithm is dead simple: for each document, walk every key recursively across base/ours/theirs and compare. That's it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":142,"cache_read_input_tokens":19932,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":142},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"44ec2dd0-de43-47c9-ba1e-ff561e90e6e4","uuid":"91884744-a4c5-4610-b779-1de303f8e873"}
